    <item>
      <title>At Easter, the accounts don't match… so who's lying?</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Join us to investigate the clues left at the empty tomb.<br/><br/>Four accounts. One empty tomb. The witnesses don't agree on the most important detail: what they actually saw that Sunday morning.<br/><br/>The tomb was sealed by Roman soldiers, but the body vanished. The resurrection case has 4 eyewitnesses, but their accounts seem to contradict each other. Who arrived first? What did they see? In this documentary, we investigate the evidence of this 2,000-year-old mystery to understand what really happened that Sunday morning.<br/><br/>If you enjoy exploring the lesser-known side of the Bible, subscribe and hit the bell. New episodes every Tuesday and Sunday.<br/><br/><br/><br/> #Resurrection #BibleMysteries #EmptyTomb #featherStoriesGroup]]></description>
